            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Florence Cathedral - The most prominent Gothic architectural work in Italy</b>: Florence Cathedral was built during the Renaissance, featuring a dome design and unique Gothic style. If you have arrived here, you should also stop by to admire the immense vineyards or famous wineries.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Colosseum - The most unique ancient Roman architectural work in the world</b>: although now only ruins remain, the Colosseum is still a symbol proving the greatness and magnanimity of the Roman Empire. is a beautiful and unique ancient architectural work left in the world. Coming to Italy and skipping the Colosseum will be a tourist's biggest mistake.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Basilica of St. Mark - The largest gold-plated structure in Italy</b>: St. Mark's Palace was built in the ancient Byzantine architectural style, with a unique dome and beautiful mosaics, where many other priceless artifacts are kept. In particular, some of the cathedral's towers are plated with shiny gold. On summer afternoons, these towers sparkle and look beautiful under the sunlight.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Leaning Tower of Pisa - Symbol of Italy</b>: if French tourism is famous for the Eiffel Tower, British tourism is famous for Big Ben, then when it comes to the list of famous tourist attractions in Italy, people immediately think of the leaning tower of Pisa. The Tower of Pisa was built in the 12th century, its original shape is not much different from other towers. But because it was built on ground that subsided over time, the tower has the characteristic tilted shape it has today.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Trevi Fountain - The most magnificent sculpture in Rome</b>: in Italy there are many famous architectural works, of which Trevi Fountain is the most unique and magnificent sculpture, attracting thousands Tourists come to visit every year. In the Trevi fountain, the statues of Neptune, Tritons, seahorses, young women... are carved extremely meticulously from limestone and Carrara marble.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Amalfi Coast - The most beautiful beach in Italy</b>: beautiful Amalfi Coast with beautiful rocky beaches, a small town with unique architecture built on the side of hills and cliffs. In particular, the seafood here is also very fresh and cheap. Visitors can both admire the beautiful scenery of Amalfi and enjoy exquisite cuisine. Visiting some towns buried in volcanoes will be a wonderful experience. when traveling in Italy.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Characteristics of staying in Italy</p>
