            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Hotels in Rome such as</b>: Grand Hotel Beverly Hills, Viminale Hotel, Hilton Garden Inn Rome</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Hotels in Milan include</b>: Ramada Plaza Milano Hotel, Armani Hotel Milano, World Hotel Cristoforo Colombo.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">In addition, in Venice, Florence, Pisa... there are many cheap hotels and motels, you can refer to them for more information.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Cuisine</p>
            <img src="~/Content/Images/Home/Handbook/Italy/italy-7.jpg" width="100%" />
            <p class="note-img">Pizza</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Pizza</b>: pizza is a famous dish around the world and is known to many people. However, not everyone knows that the homeland of Pizza is Naples - the first seaport city of the Mediterranean.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Spaghetti</b>: also known as Spaghetti, spaghetti is made from semolina flour and water with small, round strands. Spaghetti is often cooked with tomato sauce and many other spices such as oregano, basil, olive oil, meat, etc. When eating, people will sprinkle on the surface of the noodles some types of grated cheese such as Pecorino Romano, Parmedan. and Asiago. Coming to Italy without trying this dish is like not really coming to Italy.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Grilled pork with orange sauce</b>: This dish sounds complicated but is prepared quite simply and does not take much time. People use a piece of pork, marinated with chopped celery, wrapped with thinly sliced ​​salted meat, then tied tightly and fried until golden in olive oil.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Ravioli noodles with spinach and Ricotta cheese</b>: this is a long-standing traditional dish in Italy, this dish first appeared in the 13th century, over the years the dish has been transformed to suit the taste of each region.</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2"><b>Sicil Cannoli</b>: This cake is made by the Sicil people, is one of the famous cakes in Italy and is used a lot in festivals.</p>

            <p class="handbook-title-1 mt-3">Currency used in Italy</p>
            <p class="handbook-content-1 mt-2">Italy belongs to the European Union, so they use the common currency Euro. You should change to Euro currency to spend while traveling in Italy. Additionally, you can also use a credit card to pay your bill.</p>

